<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="115" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="115">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="115">
<taxonomicName authorityName="T. E. Almeida" authorityYear="2017" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Adetogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Adetogramma" order="Polypodiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="115">Adetogramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Microgramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Microgramma" order="Polypodiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="115">Microgramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Pleopeltis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pleopeltis" order="Polypodiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="115" phylum="Pteridophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="115">Pleopeltis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its epiphytic habit, long-creeping rhizomes and in having entire leaves with one row of sori on each side of the midrib, but differs from these genera by having free veins (vs. veins anastomosing in 
<taxonomicName class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Microgramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Microgramma" order="Polypodiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="115">Microgramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Pleopeltis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pleopeltis" order="Polypodiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="115" phylum="Pteridophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="115">Pleopeltis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and peltate, pedicellate, lanceolate paraphyses (vs. hairlike or lanceolate and sessile paraphyses in 
<taxonomicName class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Microgramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Microgramma" order="Polypodiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="115">Microgramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and round, peltate, pedicellate paraphyses in 
<taxonomicName class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Pleopeltis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pleopeltis" order="Polypodiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="115" phylum="Pteridophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="115">Pleopeltis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
